<br>
to continue my notion, manaburn ahs 'no' or '1' point of aggro. look at its base1, and it is a nuke. When they broke our aggro, I was one to believe that all of the damage multipliers - crits, focus, manaburn multiplier - were now giving aggro. to substantiate my notion of this being true, I looked to the rain's aggro intersects(with another plot of aggro) and found that it was very close to the base1 of a rain spell.<br>
<br>
This heralds my uncertainty- field tests indicate the aggro of the rains to be 41.6% of what it'd be if the rain aggrod like a normal nuke. That I found the same number(roughly) from different types of tests - tripong, doubled summons, aggro calculated intersects - indicates the methods used were somewhat precise... the base1 is a mystery to me. the base1 of a nuke is its dmg, of course. this is my theory- take it for what you will. common practice indicates that rains produce a greatly lessened amount of aggro... this is only my attempt to explain how much.<br>
<br>
this falls into the camp of aconcs being resisted. we don't have the information about the way the aggro works. I can play my wizard with either opinion in mind, and another shall have no concrete ability to criticize the way I play- only their differing, unsubstantiated opinion. However,  I can lend advice and leave that ultimate choice up to the wizard who is playing. I can play and perfect and what is perfected in game is true to have worked as I intended it, when it is successful. Additionally, I can lend my findings and advice to others. If you choose to trust my method or conjecture, it's your choice. I'll always try to provide you with how I came to the conclusion.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nadiar>Nadiar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.nadiar.com/avatar.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Mistyr Smartipants</span><br>  Posts: 1022<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/18/03 6:58:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25467.topic&index=75>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nadiar.com/avatar.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~</span><hr size=1> In the event of a nuke, Base1 is the BASE DAMAGE. That is how lucy determines how much damage a DD spell does.  For EVERY DD SPELL IN THE GAME it is identical.  Rains are NO DIFFERENT they represent 3 rains, of a base damage (in the case of Tears of Marr, you have 850 damage base (as determined by looking at Base1).<br>
