<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And 3 draughts is higher chance to crit, lower chance to resist, and less aggro. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
All other factors even, crits add the same percentage of damage to all spells. If you crit 19% of the time on your draughts and 19% on your SoS's ... you add 19% total damage to your bottom line, either way. You'll will have MORE crits with draughts, but less added damage every time. Any good parser will show you that.<br>
<br>
Even though you crit more often, it's not a higher chance. Crits are an awesome aa because they effect all DD spells exactly the same.<br>
<br>
